# Root .dockerignore (AE-0189)
#
# The backend image builds with `context: .` (repo root), so this root-level
# .dockerignore is the one that actually trims the build context. backend/.dockerignore
# is ineffective for that build because the context is the repo root, not backend/.
# The frontend image uses `context: ./frontend`, so it is governed by
# frontend/.dockerignore and is unaffected by the patterns below.
#
# Goal: keep the backend build context small (it was uploading ~1.2GB incl.
# frontend/node_modules). Do NOT exclude anything the backend Dockerfile COPYs:
#   - backend/pyproject.toml, backend/uv.lock
#   - backend/src/
#   - backend/alembic/, backend/alembic.ini
#   - skills/runtime/
#   - frontend/public/about-pedro.jpg  (runtime asset; *.png is excluded but this is .jpg)
#   - README.md

# Frontend build artifacts (never needed by the backend image)
frontend/node_modules
frontend/.next

# Virtualenvs / Python caches
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache

# Node modules anywhere
**/node_modules

# VCS
.git

# Images (about-pedro.jpg is a .jpg and is intentionally NOT matched here)
*.png

# Docs and scratch dirs
docs/
tmp/

# Backend tests are not needed at runtime
backend/tests/

# Env files (never bake secrets into an image)
.env*
